# Modern Web Development Best Practices

## Performance & Core Web Vitals
- **Optimize images**: Use Next.js Image component with proper sizing, lazy loading, and modern formats (WebP, AVIF)
- **Code splitting**: Implement dynamic imports and route-based code splitting
- **Bundle optimization**: Minimize bundle size, tree-shake unused code, and use proper chunking strategies
- **Caching**: Implement proper HTTP caching headers, service workers, and CDN strategies
- **Core Web Vitals**: Optimize LCP (<2.5s), FID (<100ms), CLS (<0.1)

## Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)
- **Semantic HTML**: Use proper heading hierarchy (h1-h6), landmarks, and semantic elements
- **ARIA attributes**: Implement proper ARIA labels, roles, and states for interactive elements
- **Keyboard navigation**: Ensure all interactive elements are keyboard accessible
- **Color contrast**: Maintain minimum 4.5:1 contrast ratio for normal text, 3:1 for large text
- **Screen reader support**: Provide alt text for images, descriptive link text, and form labels

## Security Best Practices
- **Input validation**: Sanitize and validate all user inputs on both client and server
- **Authentication**: Use secure session management, JWT tokens, and proper password hashing
- **HTTPS**: Enforce HTTPS in production with proper SSL/TLS configuration
- **CSP**: Implement Content Security Policy headers to prevent XSS attacks
- **Dependencies**: Regularly update dependencies and audit for vulnerabilities

## Code Quality & Maintainability
- **TypeScript**: Use strict TypeScript configuration with proper type definitions
- **ESLint/Prettier**: Enforce consistent code style and catch potential issues
- **Testing**: Implement unit tests, integration tests, and E2E tests where appropriate
- **Error handling**: Implement proper error boundaries and graceful error handling
- **Documentation**: Write clear, self-documenting code with JSDoc comments

## Modern React/Next.js Patterns
- **Server Components**: Use React Server Components for better performance and SEO
- **App Router**: Leverage Next.js 13+ App Router for improved routing and layouts
- **Streaming**: Implement streaming SSR for faster page loads
- **Middleware**: Use Next.js middleware for authentication, redirects, and request processing
- **API Routes**: Follow RESTful conventions and implement proper error handling

## Database & Data Management
- **ORM Best Practices**: Use Prisma with proper schema design and query optimization
- **Database Security**: Implement proper connection pooling, prepared statements, and access controls
- **Data Validation**: Validate data at both API and database levels
- **Migrations**: Use proper database migration strategies for schema changes

## SEO & Meta Tags
- **Structured Data**: Implement JSON-LD structured data for better search visibility
- **Meta Tags**: Use proper title, description, and Open Graph tags
- **Sitemap**: Generate and maintain XML sitemaps
- **Robots.txt**: Configure proper robots.txt for search engine crawling

## Development Workflow
- **Git**: Use conventional commits, proper branching strategies, and code reviews
- **CI/CD**: Implement automated testing, linting, and deployment pipelines
- **Environment Management**: Use proper environment variable management
- **Monitoring**: Implement error tracking, performance monitoring, and analytics
